Package: bluffbench2
Title: An Eval Measuring Whether Agents Notice What's Actually in a Plot
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Simon", "Couch", , "simon.couch@posit.co", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A multi-turn, artifact-driven evaluation of language models'
    willingness to pause and examine plots during routine data analysis.
    Agents are situated in a realistic harness, walked through a few
    unremarkable plotting requests, and then asked to make a plot containing
    a counterintuitive or anomalous artifact. The eval measures whether the
    agent notices and accurately describes the artifact. A harder, more
    realistic successor to bluffbench.
